 RBAC in Kubernetes lets you control who can do what in your cluster. It uses four main components:
Role â€“ defines permissions (verbs on resources) within a namespace.
ClusterRole â€“ defines global permissions across the whole cluster.
RoleBinding â€“ assigns a Role to a user or service account in a namespace.
